data.description:
Come home to this beautiful sanctuary nestled in the quiet, North Columbus, Bunker Hill community. Located just 13 minutes from Columbus Air Force Base, this home offers a spacious two-story, three-bedroom floor plan with an office and oversized, two-car garage. The front porch is perfect for lounging in the summertime, and the trees in the front yard are spaced perfectly for a hammock or walking across the small bridge. The 1.5 acre lot also has a fully enclosed backyard, offering plenty of room for the kids or dogs to run. Bunker Hill Road forms a one-mile loop with very light vehicle traffic that is excellent for dog-walking or running.

Inside, the kitchen and master bathroom boast large granite countertops. The upstairs bathroom has a finished storage room attached; big enough to be an activity room if desired. The master closet has been newly remodeled which offers you more storage space. The front flowerbed has been updated to add more curb appeal. The majority of the windows in the house were replaced with new ones and comes with a warranty. 

Downstairs, wood laminate floors are prominently displayed throughout the foyer, dining room, kitchen, living room, study, and half bath. 

This is a beautiful, must-see home!
